    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-04T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-04T01:00:00-05:00" n="266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1574: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-04T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 4, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Reference my No. 5, January 3, 3 p.m., paragraph 3. American Marine Commander
                    states the subject has not been discussed during the conferences held by the
                    military commanders and that such matters not being within his jurisdiction will
                    when they come up be referred to me.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
